element.name: Early Days by Windsockers, Unknown Cache (2.5/1.5)

long-description.p: Early Days indeed the above location is not the location you need in order to find this cache.

It was the location for an old cache called “Smooth Waters”
“you need to jump the wall after the horse and make your way to the middle of the bridge. Careful, it's a bit prickly where the cache is.”
there were five finds on the cache with one Cacher being confronted by the lady of the garden saying it was “private property”

The hint for the cache reads,the ways of every ingenious game has to out number every finder in very evasive numerals or under go hard times. Obtaining no effort need over upset great heads to find it very easy or need ever notice it's numeric efficiency.
Anyway there’s no Jumping walls or horse’s or bridges this time, it’s just a simple cache and dash.
The cache is a small container byop

ul.li:
2009-10-31T19:00:00Z : Found it by daraconn
Found at last! My previous unsuccessful visit to the location was over a year ago. The puzzle wasn't the hard part; the ivy was! There were a couple of windsurfers packing up while I was searching. When I was walking back along the road one of them asked me if I was geocaching. He said a friend of his does a bit of caching and that's how he knows. Stupidly I didn't ask who his friend was! Anyway I'm glad to be able to cross this one off my list. Thanks, Dara.

2009-05-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by Donnacha
Found while out and about today. This one has been sitting on my desk for a while (like all puzzle caches!) so it's good to get it off it to make room for...erm...another puzzle cache. Thanks.

2009-01-12T20:00:00Z : Found it by Bootle
Success! Each Cache Often Needs Dedication! Today, In Minutes, Eoin Located Unknown Cache! Kool! Yippee!

2009-01-02T20:00:00Z : Found it by toczygroszek
This time found after 10 minutes searching. 1st cache of new year and 100th of this owner. TFTC

2008-12-31T20:00:00Z : Didn't find it by toczygroszek
Unfortunately DNF this time. I don't like this type of hiding. Only good news for my - it was last DNF this year [:)]
